733 switch (Mnemonic[3]) {

739 return;
740 case 'l': // 2 strings to match.

744 if (Mnemonic[5] != 'l')

748 case 'h': // 1 string to match.

751 Mnemonic = "jgnlh"; // "brnlhl"
752 return;
753 }
754 break;
755 }
756 break;

1959
1960void SystemZAsmParser::
1961convertToMCInst(unsigned Kind, MCInst &Inst, unsigned Opcode,
1962 const OperandVector &Operands) {
1963 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
1964 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
1965 unsigned OpIdx;
1966 Inst.setOpcode(Opcode);
1967 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
1968 OpIdx = *(p + 1);
1969 switch (*p) {
1970 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid conversion entry!");
1971 case CVT_Reg:
1972 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1973 break;
1974 case CVT_Tied: {
1975 assert(OpIdx < (size_t)(std::end(TiedAsmOperandTable) -
1976 std::begin(TiedAsmOperandTable)) &&
1977 "Tied operand not found");
1978 unsigned TiedResOpnd = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][0];
1979 if (TiedResOpnd != (uint8_t)-1)
1980 Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(TiedResOpnd));
1981 break;
1982 }
1983 case CVT_95_addRegOperands:
1984 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
1985 break;
1986 case CVT_95_addBDXAddrOperands:
1987 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addBDXAddrOperands(Inst, 3);
1988 break;
1989 case CVT_95_addImmOperands:
1990 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
1991 break;
1992 case CVT_95_addBDAddrOperands:
1993 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addBDAddrOperands(Inst, 2);
1994 break;
1995 case CVT_95_addBDLAddrOperands:
1996 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addBDLAddrOperands(Inst, 3);
1997 break;
1998 case CVT_95_addImmTLSOperands:
1999 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addImmTLSOperands(Inst, 2);
2000 break;
2001 case CVT_imm_95_0:
2002 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
2003 break;
2004 case CVT_95_addBDRAddrOperands:
2005 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addBDRAddrOperands(Inst, 3);
2006 break;
2007 case CVT_regR0D:
2008 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(SystemZ::R0D));
2009 break;
2010 case CVT_95_addBDVAddrOperands:
2011 static_cast<SystemZOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addBDVAddrOperands(Inst, 3);
2012 break;
2013 }
2014 }
2015}
2016
2017void SystemZAsmParser::
2018convertToMapAndConstraints(unsigned Kind,
2019 const OperandVector &Operands) {
2020 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
2021 unsigned NumMCOperands = 0;
2022 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
2023 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
2024 switch (*p) {
2025 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid conversion entry!");
2026 case CVT_Reg:
2027 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2028 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("r");
2029 ++NumMCOperands;
2030 break;
2031 case CVT_Tied:
2032 ++NumMCOperands;
2033 break;
2034 case CVT_95_addRegOperands:
2035 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2036 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2037 NumMCOperands += 1;
2038 break;
2039 case CVT_95_addBDXAddrOperands:
2040 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2041 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2042 NumMCOperands += 3;
2043 break;
2044 case CVT_95_addImmOperands:
2045 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2046 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2047 NumMCOperands += 1;
2048 break;
2049 case CVT_95_addBDAddrOperands:
2050 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2051 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2052 NumMCOperands += 2;
2053 break;
2054 case CVT_95_addBDLAddrOperands:
2055 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2056 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2057 NumMCOperands += 3;
2058 break;
2059 case CVT_95_addImmTLSOperands:
2060 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2061 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2062 NumMCOperands += 2;
2063 break;
2064 case CVT_imm_95_0:
2065 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2066 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("");
2067 ++NumMCOperands;
2068 break;
2069 case CVT_95_addBDRAddrOperands:
2070 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2071 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2072 NumMCOperands += 3;
2073 break;
2074 case CVT_regR0D:
2075 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2076 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2077 ++NumMCOperands;
2078 break;
2079 case CVT_95_addBDVAddrOperands:
2080 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2081 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2082 NumMCOperands += 3;
2083 break;
2084 }
2085 }

2179/// isSubclass - Compute whether \p A is a subclass of \p B.
2180static bool isSubclass(MatchClassKind A, MatchClassKind B) {
2181 if (A == B)
2182 return true;
2183
2184 switch (A) {
2185 default:
2186 return false;
2187
2188 case MCK_ADDR128Bit:
2189 return B == MCK_GR128Bit;
2190
2191 case MCK_ADDR32Bit:
2192 switch (B) {
2193 default: return false;
2194 case MCK_GR32Bit: return true;
2195 case MCK_GRX32Bit: return true;
2196 }
2197
2198 case MCK_ADDR64Bit:
2199 switch (B) {
2200 default: return false;
2201 case MCK_GR64Bit: return true;
2202 case MCK_AnyRegBit: return true;
2203 }
2204
2205 case MCK_FP32Bit:
2206 return B == MCK_VR32Bit;
2207
2208 case MCK_FP64Bit:
2209 switch (B) {
2210 default: return false;
2211 case MCK_Reg13: return true;
2212 case MCK_VR64Bit: return true;
2213 case MCK_AnyRegBit: return true;
2214 }
2215
2216 case MCK_GR32Bit:
2217 return B == MCK_GRX32Bit;
2218
2219 case MCK_GR64Bit:
2220 return B == MCK_AnyRegBit;
2221
2222 case MCK_GRH32Bit:
2223 return B == MCK_GRX32Bit;
2224
2225 case MCK_VF128Bit:
2226 switch (B) {
2227 default: return false;
2228 case MCK_Reg13: return true;
2229 case MCK_VR128Bit: return true;
2230 case MCK_AnyRegBit: return true;
2231 }
2232
2233 case MCK_Reg13:
2234 return B == MCK_AnyRegBit;
2235 }
2236}

2238static unsigned validateOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &GOp, MatchClassKind Kind) {
2239 SystemZOperand &Operand = (SystemZOperand &)GOp;
2240 if (Kind == InvalidMatchClass)
2241 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;
2242
2243 if (Operand.isToken() && Kind <= MCK_LAST_TOKEN)
2244 return isSubclass(matchTokenString(Operand.getToken()), Kind) ?
2245 MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success :
2246 MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;

2248 switch (Kind) {

2954
2955static bool checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(const SystemZAsmParser&AsmParser,
2956 unsigned Kind,
2957 const OperandVector &Operands,
2958 uint64_t &ErrorInfo) {
2959 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
2960 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
2961 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
2962 switch (*p) {
2963 case CVT_Tied: {
2964 unsigned OpIdx = *(p + 1);
2965 assert(OpIdx < (size_t)(std::end(TiedAsmOperandTable) -
2966 std::begin(TiedAsmOperandTable)) &&
2967 "Tied operand not found");
2968 unsigned OpndNum1 = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][1];
2969 unsigned OpndNum2 = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][2];
2970 if (OpndNum1 != OpndNum2) {
2971 auto &SrcOp1 = Operands[OpndNum1];
2972 auto &SrcOp2 = Operands[OpndNum2];
2973 if (SrcOp1->isReg() && SrcOp2->isReg()) {
2974 if (!AsmParser.regsEqual(*SrcOp1, *SrcOp2)) {
2975 ErrorInfo = OpndNum2;
2976 return false;
2977 }
2978 }
2979 }
2980 break;
2981 }
2982 default:
2983 break;
2984 }
2985 }
2986 return true;
2987}

3397 return LHS < RHS.getMnemonic();
3398 }

5962
5963#include "llvm/Support/Debug.h"
5964#include "llvm/Support/Format.h"
5965
5966unsigned SystemZAsmParser::
5967MatchInstructionImpl(const OperandVector &Operands,
5968 MCInst &Inst,
5969 uint64_t &ErrorInfo,
5970 FeatureBitset &MissingFeatures,
5971 bool matchingInlineAsm, unsigned VariantID) {
5972 // Eliminate obvious mismatches.
5973 if (Operands.size() > 7) {
5974 ErrorInfo = 7;
5975 return Match_InvalidOperand;
5976 }
5977
5978 // Get the current feature set.
5979 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures = getAvailableFeatures();
5980
5981 // Get the instruction mnemonic, which is the first token.
5982 StringRef Mnemonic = ((SystemZOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken();
5983
5984 // Process all MnemonicAliases to remap the mnemonic.
5985 applyMnemonicAliases(Mnemonic, AvailableFeatures, VariantID);
5986
5987 // Some state to try to produce better error messages.
5988 bool HadMatchOtherThanFeatures = false;
5989 bool HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = false;
5990 unsigned RetCode = Match_InvalidOperand;
5991 MissingFeatures.set();
5992 // Set ErrorInfo to the operand that mismatches if it is
5993 // wrong for all instances of the instruction.
5994 ErrorInfo = ~0ULL;
5995 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
5996 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
5997 switch (VariantID) {
5998 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
5999 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
6000 }
6001 // Search the table.
6002 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
6003
6004 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "AsmMatcher: found " <<
6005 std::distance(MnemonicRange.first, MnemonicRange.second) <<
6006 " encodings with mnemonic '" << Mnemonic << "'\n");
6007
6008 // Return a more specific error code if no mnemonics match.
6009 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
6010 return Match_MnemonicFail;
6011
6012 for (const MatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first, *ie = MnemonicRange.second;
6013 it != ie; ++it) {
6014 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
6015 bool HasRequiredFeatures =
6016 (AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) == RequiredFeatures;
6017 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Trying to match opcode "
6018 << MII.getName(it->Opcode) << "\n");
6019 // equal_range guarantees that instruction mnemonic matches.
6020 assert(Mnemonic == it->getMnemonic());
6021 bool OperandsValid = true;
6022 for (unsigned FormalIdx = 0, ActualIdx = 1; FormalIdx != 6; ++FormalIdx) {
6023 auto Formal = static_cast<MatchClassKind>(it->Classes[FormalIdx]);
6024 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
6025 dbgs() << " Matching formal operand class " << getMatchClassName(Formal)
6026 << " against actual operand at index " << ActualIdx);
6027 if (ActualIdx < Operands.size())
6028 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << " (";
6029 Operands[ActualIdx]->print(dbgs()); dbgs() << "): ");
6030 else
6031 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << ": ");
6032 if (ActualIdx >= Operands.size()) {
6033 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "actual operand index out of range ");
6034 OperandsValid = (Formal == InvalidMatchClass) || isSubclass(Formal, OptionalMatchClass);
6035 if (!OperandsValid) ErrorInfo = ActualIdx;
6036 break;
6037 }
6038 MCParsedAsmOperand &Actual = *Operands[ActualIdx];
6039 unsigned Diag = validateOperandClass(Actual, Formal);
6040 if (Diag == Match_Success) {
6041 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
6042 dbgs() << "match success using generic matcher\n");
6043 ++ActualIdx;
6044 continue;
6045 }
6046 // If the generic handler indicates an invalid operand
6047 // failure, check for a special case.
6048 if (Diag != Match_Success) {
6049 unsigned TargetDiag = validateTargetOperandClass(Actual, Formal);
6050 if (TargetDiag == Match_Success) {
6051 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
6052 dbgs() << "match success using target matcher\n");
6053 ++ActualIdx;
6054 continue;
6055 }
6056 // If the target matcher returned a specific error code use
6057 // that, else use the one from the generic matcher.
6058 if (TargetDiag != Match_InvalidOperand && HasRequiredFeatures)
6059 Diag = TargetDiag;
6060 }
6061 // If current formal operand wasn't matched and it is optional
6062 // then try to match next formal operand
6063 if (Diag == Match_InvalidOperand && isSubclass(Formal, OptionalMatchClass)) {
6064 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "ignoring optional operand\n");
6065 continue;
6066 }
6067 // If this operand is broken for all of the instances of this
6068 // mnemonic, keep track of it so we can report loc info.
6069 // If we already had a match that only failed due to a
6070 // target predicate, that diagnostic is preferred.
6071 if (!HadMatchOtherThanPredicate &&
6072 (it == MnemonicRange.first || ErrorInfo <= ActualIdx)) {
6073 if (HasRequiredFeatures && (ErrorInfo != ActualIdx || Diag != Match_InvalidOperand))
6074 RetCode = Diag;
6075 ErrorInfo = ActualIdx;
6076 }
6077 // Otherwise, just reject this instance of the mnemonic.
6078 OperandsValid = false;
6079 break;
6080 }
6081
6082 if (!OperandsValid) {
6083 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Opcode result: multiple "
6084 "operand mismatches, ignoring "
6085 "this opcode\n");
6086 continue;
6087 }
6088 if (!HasRequiredFeatures) {
6089 HadMatchOtherThanFeatures = true;
6090 FeatureBitset NewMissingFeatures = RequiredFeatures & ~AvailableFeatures;
6091 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Missing target features:";
6092 for (unsigned I = 0, E = NewMissingFeatures.size(); I != E; ++I)
6093 if (NewMissingFeatures[I])
6094 dbgs() << ' ' << I;
6095 dbgs() << "\n");
6096 if (NewMissingFeatures.count() <=
6097 MissingFeatures.count())
6098 MissingFeatures = NewMissingFeatures;
6099 continue;
6100 }
6101
6102 Inst.clear();
6103
6104 Inst.setOpcode(it->Opcode);
6105 // We have a potential match but have not rendered the operands.
6106 // Check the target predicate to handle any context sensitive
6107 // constraints.
6108 // For example, Ties that are referenced multiple times must be
6109 // checked here to ensure the input is the same for each match
6110 // constraints. If we leave it any later the ties will have been
6111 // canonicalized
6112 unsigned MatchResult;
6113 if ((MatchResult = checkEarlyTargetMatchPredicate(Inst, Operands)) != Match_Success) {
6114 Inst.clear();
6115 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
6116 "asm-matcher",
6117 dbgs() << "Early target match predicate failed with diag code "
6118 << MatchResult << "\n");
6119 RetCode = MatchResult;
6120 HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = true;
6121 continue;
6122 }
6123
6124 if (matchingInlineAsm) {
6125 convertToMapAndConstraints(it->ConvertFn, Operands);
6126 if (!checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(*this, it->ConvertFn, Operands, ErrorInfo))
6127 return Match_InvalidTiedOperand;
6128
6129 return Match_Success;
6130 }
6131
6132 // We have selected a definite instruction, convert the parsed
6133 // operands into the appropriate MCInst.
6134 convertToMCInst(it->ConvertFn, Inst, it->Opcode, Operands);
6135
6136 // We have a potential match. Check the target predicate to
6137 // handle any context sensitive constraints.
6138 if ((MatchResult = checkTargetMatchPredicate(Inst)) != Match_Success) {
6139 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
6140 dbgs() << "Target match predicate failed with diag code "
6141 << MatchResult << "\n");
6142 Inst.clear();
6143 RetCode = MatchResult;
6144 HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = true;
6145 continue;
6146 }
6147
6148 if (!checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(*this, it->ConvertFn, Operands, ErrorInfo))
6149 return Match_InvalidTiedOperand;
6150
6151 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
6152 "asm-matcher",
6153 dbgs() << "Opcode result: complete match, selecting this opcode\n");
6154 return Match_Success;
6155 }
6156
6157 // Okay, we had no match. Try to return a useful error code.
6158 if (HadMatchOtherThanPredicate || !HadMatchOtherThanFeatures)
6159 return RetCode;
6160
6161 ErrorInfo = 0;
6162 return Match_MissingFeature;
6163}
6164
6165namespace {
6166 struct OperandMatchEntry {
6167 uint16_t Mnemonic;
6168 uint8_t OperandMask;
6169 uint8_t Class;
6170 uint8_t RequiredFeaturesIdx;
6171
6172 StringRef getMnemonic() const {
6173 return StringRef(MnemonicTable + Mnemonic + 1,
6174 MnemonicTable[Mnemonic]);
6175 }
6176 };
6177
6178 // Predicate for searching for an opcode.
6179 struct LessOpcodeOperand {
6180 bool operator()(const OperandMatchEntry &LHS, StringRef RHS) {
6181 return LHS.getMnemonic() < RHS;
6182 }
6183 bool operator()(StringRef LHS, const OperandMatchEntry &RHS) {
6184 return LHS < RHS.getMnemonic();
6185 }
6186 bool operator()(const OperandMatchEntry &LHS, const OperandMatchEntry &RHS) {
6187 return LHS.getMnemonic() < RHS.getMnemonic();
6188 }
6189 };
6190} // end anonymous namespace

9840
9841OperandMatchResultTy SystemZAsmParser::
9842MatchOperandParserImpl(OperandVector &Operands,
9843 StringRef Mnemonic,
9844 bool ParseForAllFeatures) {
9845 // Get the current feature set.
9846 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures = getAvailableFeatures();
9847
9848 // Get the next operand index.
9849 unsigned NextOpNum = Operands.size() - 1;
9850 // Search the table.
9851 auto MnemonicRange =
9852 std::equal_range(std::begin(OperandMatchTable), std::end(OperandMatchTable),
9853 Mnemonic, LessOpcodeOperand());
9854
9855 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
9856 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
9857
9858 for (const OperandMatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first,
9859 *ie = MnemonicRange.second; it != ie; ++it) {
9860 // equal_range guarantees that instruction mnemonic matches.
9861 assert(Mnemonic == it->getMnemonic());
9862
9863 // check if the available features match
9864 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
9865 if (!ParseForAllFeatures && (AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) != RequiredFeatures)
9866 continue;
9867
9868 // check if the operand in question has a custom parser.
9869 if (!(it->OperandMask & (1 << NextOpNum)))
9870 continue;
9871
9872 // call custom parse method to handle the operand
9873 OperandMatchResultTy Result = tryCustomParseOperand(Operands, it->Class);
9874 if (Result != MatchOperand_NoMatch)
9875 return Result;
9876 }
9877
9878 // Okay, we had no match.
9879 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
9880}

9882#endif // GET_MATCHER_IMPLEMENTATION

9885#ifdef GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
9886#undef GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
9887
9888static std::string SystemZMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S, const FeatureBitset &FBS, unsigned VariantID) {
9889 const unsigned MaxEditDist = 2;
9890 std::vector<StringRef> Candidates;
9891 StringRef Prev = "";
9892
9893 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
9894 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
9895 switch (VariantID) {
9896 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
9897 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
9898 }
9899
9900 for (auto I = Start; I < End; I++) {
9901 // Ignore unsupported instructions.
9902 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[I->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
9903 if ((FBS & RequiredFeatures) != RequiredFeatures)
9904 continue;
9905
9906 StringRef T = I->getMnemonic();
9907 // Avoid recomputing the edit distance for the same string.
9908 if (T.equals(Prev))
9909 continue;
9910
9911 Prev = T;
9912 unsigned Dist = S.edit_distance(T, false, MaxEditDist);
9913 if (Dist <= MaxEditDist)
9914 Candidates.push_back(T);
9915 }
9916
9917 if (Candidates.empty())
9918 return "";
9919
9920 std::string Res = ", did you mean: ";
9921 unsigned i = 0;
9922 for (; i < Candidates.size() - 1; i++)
9923 Res += Candidates[i].str() + ", ";
9924 return Res + Candidates[i].str() + "?";
9925}
9926
9927#endif // GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER

9930#ifdef GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
9931#undef GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
9932
9933static bool SystemZCheckMnemonic(StringRef Mnemonic,
9934 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures,
9935 unsigned VariantID) {
9936 // Process all MnemonicAliases to remap the mnemonic.
9937 applyMnemonicAliases(Mnemonic, AvailableFeatures, VariantID);
9938
9939 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
9940 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
9941 switch (VariantID) {
9942 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
9943 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
9944 }
9945
9946 // Search the table.
9947 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
9948
9949 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
9950 return false;
9951
9952 for (const MatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first, *ie = MnemonicRange.second;
9953 it != ie; ++it) {
9954 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures =
9955 FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
9956 if ((AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) == RequiredFeatures)
9957 return true;
9958 }
9959 return false;
9960}

9962#endif // GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
